print("A.1.3 Forecasting Drivers of High Value (Linear Regression)")
if not df1.empty:
    features = ['Age', 'Income', 'Website_Visits', 'Average_Spend']
    target = 'Total_Spend'
    # Define predictors and target
    X = df1[features]
    y = df1[target]
     # Standardize values before regression
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)
    model_lr = LinearRegression()
    model_lr.fit(X_scaled, y)
    coefficients_1 = pd.DataFrame(model_lr.coef_, features, columns=['Coefficient'])
     # Print regression results
    print("Model Coefficients (Predictors of Total Spend)")
    print(coefficients_1.sort_values(by='Coefficient', ascending=False))
    r_squared = model_lr.score(X_scaled, y)
    print(f"\nModel R-squared: {r_squared:.2f}")
else:
    print("Skipping 1.3 (D1 not loaded)")

# A.1.4 Customer Segmentation (K-Means)
print("A.1.4 Customer Segmentation (K-Means)")

# Select and scale features
X_cluster = df1[['Income', 'Total_Spend']]
X_scaled = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X_cluster)

# Elbow Method to choose cluster number
inertia = []
for k in range(1, 10):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10)
    kmeans.fit(X_scaled)
    inertia.append(kmeans.inertia_)

plt.plot(range(1, 10), inertia, color=main_pink, marker='o', markersize=8)
plt.title('Elbow Method for Optimal k', color=dark_pink)
plt.savefig('d1_elbow_pink.png')

# Run K-Means
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=42, n_init=10)
df1['Cluster'] = kmeans.fit_predict(X_scaled)
print("Cluster Averages:\n", df1.groupby('Cluster')[['Income', 'Total_Spend']].mean())


# Scatter plot to show cluster separation
sns.scatterplot(data=df1, x='Income', y='Total_Spend', hue='Cluster',
                palette="RdPu", s=100, edgecolor='white')
plt.title('Customer Segments (k=4)', color=dark_pink)
plt.savefig('d1_clusters_pink.png')

# B.2.1 Anomaly Analysis
print("B.2.1 Anomaly Analysis")
print("Missing Values in D2")
print(df2.isnull().sum())
print("Descriptive Statistics for D2")
print(df2.describe())

df2_cleaned = df2.copy()
df2_cleaned['Error_Rate'].fillna(df2_cleaned['Error_Rate'].median(), inplace=True)
df2_cleaned['Client_Satisfaction'].fillna(df2_cleaned['Client_Satisfaction'].median(), inplace=True)
# Cap extreme error rates (above 99th percentile)
p_99 = df2_cleaned['Error_Rate'].quantile(0.99)
print(f"\n99th Percentile for Error_Rate (Capping value): {p_99:.2f}")
df2_cleaned['Error_Rate'] = df2_cleaned['Error_Rate'].apply(lambda x: p_99 if x > p_99 else x)
print("Data After Cleaning")
print(df2_cleaned.describe())

# B.2.3 Predicting 'At Risk' Employees (Logistic Regression)
print("B.2.3 Predicting 'At Risk' Employees (Logistic Regression)")
threshold = 5.0
# Create binary target: 1 = At risk, 0 = Satisfied
df2_cleaned['At_Risk'] = (df2_cleaned['Client_Satisfaction'] < threshold).astype(int)
# Build logistic regression model
X = df2_cleaned[['Hours_Worked', 'Projects_Completed', 'Error_Rate']]
y = df2_cleaned['At_Risk']
scaler_class = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler_class.fit_transform(X)
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y, test_size=0.25, random_state=42, stratify=y)
model_log = LogisticRegression(random_state=42)
model_log.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred = model_log.predict(X_test)
print("Model Validation (Classification Report)")
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
coefficients_log = pd.DataFrame(model_log.coef_[0], X.columns, columns=['Coefficient'])
print("Model Coefficients (Predictors of 'At_Risk')")
print(coefficients_log.sort_values(by='Coefficient', ascending=False))

# B.2.4 What-if: Reduce High Error Rates (Simulation)
print("B.2.4 What-if: Reduce High Error Rates (Simulation)")
# Train regression to estimate satisfaction from performance factors
if not df2_cleaned.empty:
    X_reg = df2_cleaned[['Hours_Worked', 'Projects_Completed', 'Error_Rate']]
    y_reg = df2_cleaned['Client_Satisfaction']
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_reg)
    reg = LinearRegression().fit(X_scaled, y_reg)
    df2_cleaned['Predicted_Satisfaction'] = reg.predict(X_scaled)
    df_sim = df2_cleaned.copy()
    high_error = df_sim['Error_Rate'] > 0.1
    df_sim.loc[high_error, 'Error_Rate'] *= 0.5
    df_sim['New_Predicted_Satisfaction'] = reg.predict(scaler.transform(df_sim[X_reg.columns]))
    print(f"Predicted Satisfaction Improvement: {df_sim['New_Predicted_Satisfaction'].mean() - df2_cleaned['Predicted_Satisfaction'].mean():.2f}")

B.2.4 What-if: Reduce High Error Rates (Simulation)
Predicted Satisfaction Improvement: 0.17

# C.3.3 12-Month Forecast (SARIMAX)
print("C.3.3 12-Month Forecast (SARIMAX)")
endog = df3['Monthly_Sales']
exog = df3[['Marketing_Spend', 'Seasonality_Index', 'Competitor_Price']]
model = SARIMAX(endog, exog=exog, order=(1,1,1), seasonal_order=(1,1,1,12))
res = model.fit(disp=False)
# Predict next 12 months
future_exog = exog.iloc[-12:]
forecast = res.get_forecast(steps=12, exog=future_exog).summary_frame()
plt.plot(df3['Monthly_Sales'], label='Observed', color=light_pink)
plt.plot(forecast['mean'], label='Forecast', color=dark_pink, linestyle='--')
plt.fill_between(forecast.index, forecast['mean_ci_lower'], forecast['mean_ci_upper'], color=main_pink, alpha=0.2)
plt.legend()
plt.title('12-Month Forecast', color=dark_pink)
plt.savefig('d3_forecast_pink.png')

C.3.3 12-Month Forecast (SARIMAX)

# C.3.4 'What-if' Scenario: 10% Marketing Increase
print("C.3.4 'What-if' Scenario: 10% Marketing Increase")

# Baseline 12-month forecast
forecast = res.get_forecast(steps=12, exog=exog.iloc[-12:])
forecast_df = forecast.summary_frame()
base_sales_forecast_total = forecast_df['mean'].sum()

# Create modified exogenous input
sim_exog = exog.iloc[-12:].copy()
sim_exog.loc[sim_exog.index[:3], 'Marketing_Spend'] *= 1.10   # +10% first 3 months

# New forecast with boosted marketing
forecast_sim = res.get_forecast(steps=12, exog=sim_exog)
sim_sales_forecast = forecast_sim.summary_frame()

# Compute lift
sim_sales_forecast_total = sim_sales_forecast['mean'].sum()
sales_lift = sim_sales_forecast_total - base_sales_forecast_total

print(f"Projected Sales Lift from 10% Spend: {sales_lift:.0f} units")

C.3.4 'What-if' Scenario: 10% Marketing Increase
Projected Sales Lift from 10% Spend: -13 units

X4 = df4[['Account_Balance', 'Number_of_Products', 'Online_Transactions']]
X_scaled = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X4)
# Elbow method to find optimal clusters
inertia = [KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10).fit(X_scaled).inertia_ for k in range(1, 10)]

kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=42, n_init=10)
